      </p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-700); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        The bail amount represents the financial guarantee that the defendant will appear for court. Rather than paying the full amount to the court, you can pay a percentage (typically 10%) to a bail bondsman like Angel Bail Bonds. We then guarantee the full bail amount to the court, securing your loved one's release while you handle the legal process.
      </p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-700); line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">
        Our 24/7 availability means we're here when you need us most—nights, weekends, and holidays. We accept multiple payment methods including cash, credit cards, Zelle, and Venmo, making it easier to post bail quickly. With over 15 years of experience and a 4.9/5 rating from 127 reviews, Angel Bail Bonds is Creek County's trusted choice for fast, professional bail assistance.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- About Creek County Section -->
  <div style="max-width: 1100px; margin: 3rem auto; padding: 0 1.5rem;">
    <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.875rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center;">
      About Creek County, Oklahoma
