          How much do bail bonds cost in Creek County?
        </summary>
        <div style="padding: 1.5rem; color: var(--slate-700); line-height: 1.6;">
          Bail bond fees are typically 10% of the total bail amount set by the court. For example, if bail is set at $5,000, you'd pay $500 to Angel Bail Bonds. We work with families to make bail affordable and accept multiple payment methods.
        </div>
      </details>
      <!-- FAQ 2 -->
      <details style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--slate-200);">
        <summary style="padding: 1.5rem; cursor: pointer; background-color: var(--slate-50); font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); user-select: none;">
          What is the fastest way to post bail in Sapulpa?
        </summary>
        <div style="padding: 1.5rem; color: var(--slate-700); line-height: 1.6;">
          Call Angel Bail Bonds immediately at (405) 614-3000. We can often process bail bonds over the phone with payment via credit card, Zelle, or Venmo. Once payment is confirmed, we post the bond at the jail and your loved one is typically released within 1-4 hours.
